subSubSection.paragraph:
This new species was identified as
C. weberi
several times: Edmondson 1935 , Adamson (1935 , 1939 ), Marquet (1988) , Marquet (1991) , Poupin (1998) , Keith and Vigneux (2002), Keith et al. (2002), Keith et al. (2013) . Indeed, this species looks like
C. weberi sensu stricto
by its straight or bent down rostrum, 0.3 – 0.4 of cl, (vs 0.4 in
C. weberi
) reaching to the base or middle of second segment of antennular peduncle with numerous dorsal teeth 10 – 13 (vs
10 – 19 in
C. weberi
), but differs by the presence of 0 – 3 dorsal teeth situated on carapace behind orbital margin (vs 0 in
C. weberi
). Also its P1 movable finger is shorter 0.6 – 0.9 times length of palm (vs
1.2 – 1.3 in
C. weberi
) as is its P1 carpus 1.3 – 1.7 times as long as wide (vs 1.9 – 2.0 in
C. weberi
), and its P2 carpus is longer, 5.5 – 6.6 times as long as wide (vs 4.9 – 5.0 in
C. weberi
). Furthermore, the posterior margin of the telson always shows only one pair of lateral spines (vs 2 in
C. weberi
).
